basAliasIpMib.name: basAliasIpMib
basAliasIpMib.contactinfo: Tech Support Broadband Access Systems 201 Forest Street Marlboro, MA 01752 U.S.A. 508-485-8200 support@basystems.com
basAliasIpMib.description: This MIB module defines the Alias IP MIB objects for a Broadband Access System Cluster.

basIpEntry.name: basIpEntry
basIpEntry.description: IP objects for a Chassis Stack.

basIpForwarding.name: basIpForwarding
basIpForwarding.description: The indication of whether this entity is acting as an IP router in respect to the forwarding of datagrams received by, but not addressed to, this entity. IP routers forward datagrams. IP hosts do not (except those source-routed via the host).

basIpDefaultTTL.name: basIpDefaultTTL
basIpDefaultTTL.description: The default value inserted into the Time-To-Live field of the IP header of datagrams originated at this entity, whenever a TTL value is not supplied by the transport layer protocol.

basIpInReceives.name: basIpInReceives
basIpInReceives.description: The total number of input datagrams received from interfaces, including those received in error.

basIpInHdrErrors.name: basIpInHdrErrors
basIpInHdrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including bad checksums, version number mismatch, other format errors, time-to-live exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

basIpInAddrErrors.name: basIpInAddrErrors
basIpInAddrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., 0.0.0.0) and addresses of unsupported Classes (e.g., Class E). For entities which are not IP routers and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address.

basIpForwDatagrams.name: basIpForwDatagrams
basIpForwDatagrams.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination. In entities which do not act as IP routers, this counter will include only those packets which were Source-Routed via this entity, and the Source-Route option processing was successful.

basIpInUnknownProtos.name: basIpInUnknownProtos
basIpInUnknownProtos.description: The number of locally-addressed datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

basIpInDiscards.name: basIpInDiscards
basIpInDiscards.description: The number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly.

basIpInDelivers.name: basIpInDelivers
basIpInDelivers.description: The total number of input datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP).

basIpOutRequests.name: basIpOutRequests
basIpOutRequests.description: The total number of IP datagrams which local IP user- protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams.

basIpOutDiscards.name: basIpOutDiscards
basIpOutDiscards.description: The number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but which were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter would include datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams if any such packets met this (discretionary) discard criterion.

basIpOutNoRoutes.name: basIpOutNoRoutes
basIpOutNoRoutes.description: The number of IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in ipForwDatagrams which meet this `no-route' criterion. Note that this includes any datagrams which a host cannot route because all of its default routers are down.

basIpReasmTimeout.name: basIpReasmTimeout
basIpReasmTimeout.description: The maximum number of seconds which received fragments are held while they are awaiting reassembly at this entity.

basIpReasmReqds.name: basIpReasmReqds
basIpReasmReqds.description: The number of IP fragments received which needed to be reassembled at this entity.

basIpReasmOKs.name: basIpReasmOKs
basIpReasmOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams successfully re-assembled.

basIpReasmFails.name: basIpReasmFails
basIpReasmFails.description: The number of failures detected by the IP re-assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc). Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received.

basIpFragOKs.name: basIpFragOKs
basIpFragOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented at this entity.

basIpFragFails.name: basIpFragFails
basIpFragFails.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented at this entity but could not be, e.g., because their Don't Fragment flag was set.

basIpFragCreates.name: basIpFragCreates
basIpFragCreates.description: The number of IP datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of fragmentation at this entity.

basIpChassis.name: basIpChassis
basIpChassis.description: The BAS Chassis ID of this card.

basIpSlot.name: basIpSlot
basIpSlot.description: The BAS Slot ID of this card.

basIpIf.name: basIpIf
basIpIf.description: The BAS interface ID of this card.

basIpLPort.name: basIpLPort
basIpLPort.description: The BAS logical port ID of this card.

basIcmpEntry.name: basIcmpEntry
basIcmpEntry.description: ICMP objects for a Chassis Stack.

basIcmpInMsgs.name: basIcmpInMsgs
basIcmpInMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which the entity received. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpInErrors.

basIcmpInErrors.name: basIcmpInErrors
basIcmpInErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which the entity received but determined as having ICMP-specific errors (bad ICMP checksums, bad length, etc.).

basIcmpInDestUnreachs.name: basIcmpInDestUnreachs
basIcmpInDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages received.

basIcmpInTimeExcds.name: basIcmpInTimeExcds
basIcmpInTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages received.

basIcmpInParmProbs.name: basIcmpInParmProbs
basIcmpInParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages received.

basIcmpInSrcQuenchs.name: basIcmpInSrcQuenchs
basIcmpInSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages received.

basIcmpInRedirects.name: basIcmpInRedirects
basIcmpInRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages received.

basIcmpInEchos.name: basIcmpInEchos
basIcmpInEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages received.

basIcmpInEchoReps.name: basIcmpInEchoReps
basIcmpInEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages received.

basIcmpInTimestamps.name: basIcmpInTimestamps
basIcmpInTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages received.

basIcmpInTimestampReps.name: basIcmpInTimestampReps
basIcmpInTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages received.

basIcmpInAddrMasks.name: basIcmpInAddrMasks
basIcmpInAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages received.

basIcmpInAddrMaskReps.name: basIcmpInAddrMaskReps
basIcmpInAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages received.

basIcmpOutMsgs.name: basIcmpOutMsgs
basIcmpOutMsgs.description: The total number of ICMP messages which this entity attempted to send. Note that this counter includes all those counted by icmpOutErrors.

basIcmpOutErrors.name: basIcmpOutErrors
basIcmpOutErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages which this entity did not send due to problems discovered within ICMP such as a lack of buffers. This value should not include errors discovered outside the ICMP layer such as the inability of IP to route the resultant datagram. In some implementations there may be no types of error which contribute to this counter's value.

basIcmpOutDestUnreachs.name: basIcmpOutDestUnreachs
basIcmpOutDestUnreachs.description: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages sent.

basIcmpOutTimeExcds.name: basIcmpOutTimeExcds
basIcmpOutTimeExcds.description: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages sent.

basIcmpOutParmProbs.name: basIcmpOutParmProbs
basIcmpOutParmProbs.description: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages sent.

basIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.name: basIcmpOutSrcQuenchs
basIcmpOutSrcQuenchs.description: The number of ICMP Source Quench messages sent.

basIcmpOutRedirects.name: basIcmpOutRedirects
basIcmpOutRedirects.description: The number of ICMP Redirect messages sent. For a host, this object will always be zero, since hosts do not send redirects.

basIcmpOutEchos.name: basIcmpOutEchos
basIcmpOutEchos.description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages sent.

basIcmpOutEchoReps.name: basIcmpOutEchoReps
basIcmpOutEchoReps.description: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages sent.

basIcmpOutTimestamps.name: basIcmpOutTimestamps
basIcmpOutTimestamps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp (request) messages sent.

basIcmpOutTimestampReps.name: basIcmpOutTimestampReps
basIcmpOutTimestampReps.description: The number of ICMP Timestamp Reply messages sent.

basIcmpOutAddrMasks.name: basIcmpOutAddrMasks
basIcmpOutAddrMasks.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Request messages sent.

basIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.name: basIcmpOutAddrMaskReps
basIcmpOutAddrMaskReps.description: The number of ICMP Address Mask Reply messages sent.

basIcmpChassis.name: basIcmpChassis
basIcmpChassis.description: The BAS Chassis ID of this card.

basIcmpSlot.name: basIcmpSlot
basIcmpSlot.description: The BAS Slot ID of this card.

basIcmpIf.name: basIcmpIf
basIcmpIf.description: The BAS interface ID of this card.

basIcmpLPort.name: basIcmpLPort
basIcmpLPort.description: The BAS logical port ID of this card.
